  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6604 sitting just below the massive +66B gamma wall at 6610 and well above the GEX flip at 6611, dealers are in stabilizing mode and likely selling into any strength toward 6610-6615 while providing support on dips toward 6605. The PIN regime with 147B total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, with dealers acting as liquidity providers around the current 6604-6610 range. Key inflection points are the 6590 negative gamma cluster (where dealer buying would accelerate any breakdown) and the 6611 flip strike that separates stabilizing from amplifying dealer flows.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect sideways chop between 6590-6615 with dealers capping upside and supporting dips.",
